HEADWORD: Maneh
<hw>Ma"neh</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.
<ets>m⟦amac⟧neh</ets>.]</ety> <def>A Hebrew weight for gold or silver,
being one hundred shekels of gold and sixty shekels of silver.</def>
<rj><au>Ezek. xlv. 12.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
